[Amit Varma]: One of the areas in which people had a lot of hopes of the modi government was privatization

01:06:21.020 --> 01:06:26.700
[Amit Varma]: You heard a lot about how we have so many psus and people would do draw graphs of okay

01:06:26.700 --> 01:06:32.060
[Amit Varma]: Here's how the number of psu ppsus have increased through the decades and they've actually increased even more

01:06:32.540 --> 01:06:36.220
[Amit Varma]: And you know my good friend sadhanand dhume you've quoted him in your book

01:06:36.620 --> 01:06:38.620
[Amit Varma]: Summing it all up and i'll quote him as well

01:06:39.100 --> 01:06:47.100
[Amit Varma]: Start quote in effect india's privatization program has become a dodgy accounting exercise in which one government owned entity buys stakes in another

01:06:47.100 --> 01:06:51.500
[Amit Varma]: Rather than an attempt to streamline the economy by selling unproductive assets to private bidders

01:06:52.060 --> 01:06:59.180
[Amit Varma]: Stop quote and this is really so bizarre because at least in privatization one assumed that there were a lot of low-hanging fruit

01:06:59.260 --> 01:07:02.540
[Amit Varma]: That they could just get rid of and they did absolutely nothing

01:07:03.420 --> 01:07:04.620
[Guest]: well

01:07:04.620 --> 01:07:10.540
[Guest]: yeah, and and uh again i'm puzzled because uh, I don't understand you know, if

01:07:11.080 --> 01:07:12.620
[Guest]: Prime minister modi

01:07:12.620 --> 01:07:15.100
[Guest]: Uh in his first year had made the case

01:07:15.100 --> 01:07:20.700
[Guest]: Imagine prime minister modi when he became prime minister, uh at the peak of his popularity said to the country

01:07:21.260 --> 01:07:23.660
[Guest]: Look, the congress left me a terrible

01:07:24.460 --> 01:07:26.460
[Guest]: uh problem with banks

